sections.retrieval_text:
TASKS > Receiving all Codex communications, documents and publications from the Commission;
number=(a)
level=2

TASKS > Initiating relevant action on the received documents either directly or through the National Codex Committee and/or the relevant sub-committee(s) or institution;
number=(b)
level=2

TASKS > Maintaining a library of all Codex standards, Codes of Practice, Guidelines and any other documents and publications on or relating to Codex;
number=(c)
level=2

TASKS > Distribution of Codex documents, publications and other information to all stakeholders;
number=(d)
level=2

TASKS > Acting as the link between the Codex Secretariat and Codex member countries;
number=(e)
level=2

sections.text:
It is desirable that the location meets the following criteria:
- that it is as neutral as possible as regards all interested parties’ involvement in Codex work;
- that it is capable of performing the tasks of the Codex Contact Point;
- that it is accessible to all parties interested and/or those involved in the activities of Codex.

